---
title: Chicken Under a "Brick" with Baby Broccoli, Lemon, and Fingerling Potatoes
description: Okay, so the “brick” here may just be a pot made heavy with water, but this technique is a surefire way to get chicken with an irresistibly crispy skin. Applying weight to a half-bird creates increased surface contact with the pan—and that means more opportunities for it to sizzle and seize up into a delightful golden brown. Afterward, the chicken is finished in the oven with a mix of veggies, then given a drizzle of lemon for added brightness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chicken-under-a-brick-826bd5aa.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-under-a-brick-a05d40f1.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 55 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 44 g
