author: HelloFresh
---

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Fill a #large pot{} halfway with @water{}. Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @half chicken{24%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Tuscan heat spice{1%tbsp}, then drizzle with @olive oil{1%tsp}. Massage with hands, rubbing seasonings into chicken skin.

Place chicken in pan skin-side down. Carefully place pot with water on top to weigh chicken down. Cook until skin is browned and crisp, ~{10-12%minutes}. If chicken browns too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve @white potatoes{12%oz}. Trim bottom inch from @baby broccoli{6%oz}. Halve @lemon{1}. Halve and peel @red onion{1}, then cut into ¾-inch-thick wedges. Pick @rosemary{¼%oz} leaves until you have 2 TBSP; discard stems. Toss potatoes, onion, rosemary, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} on a #baking sheet{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Place lemon halves toward edges of same baking sheet cut-side down. Lay chicken skin-side up on top of veggies in center of baking sheet. Roast in oven until no longer pink in thickest part of thigh, ~{30-40%minutes} (we'll be adding more items to the sheet before the chicken is done).

After chicken has roasted ~{20%minutes}, toss baby broccoli with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove sheet from oven and add baby broccoli to same sheet. Return to oven and continue roasting until baby broccoli is tender and chicken is done. Let rest ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven.

Insert a #knife{} between chicken thigh and breast, pulling leg away to separate into two pieces. If you would like everyone to have both dark and white meat, cut between drumstick and thigh, then divide breast in half. Divide veggies and chicken between plates. Drizzle with juice from roasted lemon.

> This technique is a surefire way to get chicken with an irresistibly crispy skin. Applying weight to a half-bird creates increased surface contact with the pan—and that means more opportunities for it to sizzle and seize up into a delightful golden brown.

> Afterward, the chicken is finished in the oven with a mix of veggies, then given a drizzle of lemon for added brightness.